<ul style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; -qt-list-indent: 1;"><li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">Without the grace of God through Jesus freeing us from sin and pardoning us, what motive is there for obedience to God outside of outright fear?</li>
<li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">The Catholic church and the heresies it teaches are at the core of missing this understanding. We are to fear the Lord, but not because we fear eternal damnation or punishment.</li>
<li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">We are to obey out of respect and gratitude for the selfless act of Jesus' suffering and death for our broken lives.</li></ul></body></html>